<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="7" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Lord</persName>.</hi><note n="b" xml:id="d7fnb">Same telegram, mutatis mutandis, to all United States
                                diplomatic representatives</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-24"><hi rend="italic">May 24,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>You are instructed, at the request of the President of Cuba, to ask the
                            Government of Argentina to permit United States consular officers within
                            its jurisdiction to use their good offices in representation of the
                            interests of Cuba and of its citizens until Cuban consuls shall have
                            been appointed.</p>
                        <p>If permission is granted, notify consuls.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>